WEBVTT

00:01.459 --> 00:04.671
♪♪

00:04.754 --> 00:07.173
♪ We are The Fungies ♪

00:07.257 --> 00:10.552
♪ Prehistoric fungi
in a mushroom to-o-wn ♪

00:10.635 --> 00:11.970
♪ Outside, we look different ♪

00:12.053 --> 00:13.596
♪ Inside, we're the same ♪
Yeah!

00:13.680 --> 00:16.099
♪ Everyone's a Fungie
in their own way ♪

00:16.182 --> 00:18.435
♪ Come join The Fungies ♪

00:18.518 --> 00:21.771
♪ Explore a brand-new world
made just for yo-o-u ♪

00:21.855 --> 00:23.440
♪ If you're inclusive,
inquisitive ♪

00:23.523 --> 00:25.024
♪ Respectful, and kind ♪

00:25.108 --> 00:28.778
♪ You can be a Fungie, too ♪

00:28.862 --> 00:35.326
♪♪

00:35.410 --> 00:37.120
Announcer:<i> In a world</i>
<i>where monsters</i>

00:37.203 --> 00:39.122
<i>have risen from the deep...</i>

00:39.205 --> 00:41.249
[ Roars ]

00:41.332 --> 00:42.876
[ Screaming ]

00:42.959 --> 00:45.420
<i>...Earth's only hope</i>
<i>for survival</i>

00:45.503 --> 00:47.672
<i>is an unlikely pair.</i>

00:47.756 --> 00:50.216
Computer:
<i>Initiate flow compatibility.</i>

00:50.300 --> 00:52.719
<i>Flow compatibility achieved.</i>

00:52.802 --> 00:54.721
Announcer:<i> Can they overcome</i>
<i>their differences</i>

00:54.804 --> 00:56.765
<i>and save us all?</i>

00:56.848 --> 00:59.350
[ Roaring ]

00:59.434 --> 01:02.604
<i>Will Tiara Thunder finally</i>
<i>learn to listen?</i>

01:02.687 --> 01:04.355
My fatal flaw --

01:04.439 --> 01:06.232
control issues.

01:06.316 --> 01:09.819
<i>Find out at the world</i>
<i>premiere of "Atlantic Edge."</i>

01:09.903 --> 01:12.322
<i>Tonight at the Fungie Dome</i>
<i>at 7:00.</i>

01:12.405 --> 01:14.157
♪ It's tonight,
it's tonight ♪

01:14.240 --> 01:15.658
♪ Tonight is the night ♪

01:15.742 --> 01:16.659
♪ Tonight ♪

01:16.743 --> 01:17.660
Whoo-hoo! [ Chuckles ]

01:17.744 --> 01:19.162
So what's tonight, baby?

01:19.245 --> 01:22.290
Me and Shania, we're going to
the "Atlantic Edge" premiere!

01:22.373 --> 01:23.958
<i>Ky-yah!</i>

01:24.042 --> 01:28.463
Well, just help me put away the
dishes before you leave, okay?

01:28.546 --> 01:30.840
Hmmm,
this calls for...

01:30.924 --> 01:32.801
a Seth solution!

01:32.884 --> 01:34.636
Hyah!

01:34.719 --> 01:43.645
♪♪

01:43.728 --> 01:45.688
And that'll do it!

01:45.772 --> 01:47.649
What would you do without me,
Mom?

01:47.732 --> 01:50.360
Well, I'd do the cooking,
the washing,

01:50.443 --> 01:52.779
and the drying
as usual,

01:52.862 --> 01:57.325
but I'd miss having somebody
do the easiest part at the end.

01:59.452 --> 02:01.204
Dang!
Better get going!

02:01.287 --> 02:06.167
♪♪

02:06.251 --> 02:07.669
Oh, hi, Seth.

02:07.752 --> 02:11.714
<i>Prepare to b-b-b-battle</i>
<i>our emotional baggage.</i>

02:11.798 --> 02:13.800
You ready for the premiere?
'Cause I am!

02:13.883 --> 02:15.802
See,
I got all my cosplay,

02:15.885 --> 02:17.887
and I wanna be first
in line for tickets!

02:17.971 --> 02:19.055
So c'mon, let's go!

02:19.138 --> 02:20.431
Sorry, I can't go.

02:20.515 --> 02:21.724
Mom and Ryan
are working late,

02:21.808 --> 02:23.768
so I gotta watch
my siblings tonight.

02:23.852 --> 02:25.144
Ahhhhh!

02:25.228 --> 02:27.522
Hey, Connor!
We just fixed that!

02:27.605 --> 02:31.067
But, Shania, we're the two
biggest "Atlantic Edge"

02:31.150 --> 02:32.527
fans in town!

02:32.610 --> 02:33.862
I wanna go,

02:33.945 --> 02:36.155
but with my parents out,
I gotta feed the kids,

02:36.239 --> 02:37.991
tire them out,
put them to bed.

02:38.074 --> 02:39.909
Hey! Spit that out!

02:39.993 --> 02:42.078
Say, I do chores.

02:42.161 --> 02:44.455
I always come up
with these Seth solutions.

02:44.539 --> 02:47.750
With my help, I bet we can
finish in time for the premiere.

02:47.834 --> 02:48.918
You sure?

02:49.002 --> 02:51.129
This might be
a little different.

02:51.212 --> 02:52.881
Just show me
what needs doing!

02:52.964 --> 02:54.424
Well, alright!

02:54.507 --> 02:56.342
[ Laughter, shouting ]

02:56.426 --> 02:58.261
Hey, guys, listen up!

02:58.344 --> 03:00.138
This is my friend Seth.

03:00.221 --> 03:01.681
Seth,
these are my siblings.

03:01.764 --> 03:04.976
Shubert, Shelly, Shimmy,
Sean, Shadi, Sheremy,

03:05.059 --> 03:08.521
Shamantha, Shuri, Connor,
and the rest.

03:08.605 --> 03:11.608
Hmm, that seems like
too many siblings.

03:11.691 --> 03:12.984
Weeeeee!

03:13.067 --> 03:15.445
[ Chuckles ] Yeah.

03:15.528 --> 03:18.740
Okay, Seth,
first we get everyone fed.

03:18.823 --> 03:22.285
Oh! At my house, that means
it's time to set the table.

03:22.368 --> 03:24.746
I bet the dishes
are in here.

03:24.829 --> 03:27.957
Whoa!

03:28.041 --> 03:29.125
Feed me, feed me.

03:29.208 --> 03:30.168
Food, food.

03:30.251 --> 03:31.586
No time to set the table.

03:31.669 --> 03:33.796
They never sit still anyway.
Nom-nom-nom-nom-nom.

03:33.880 --> 03:36.799
Just keep an eye out
for food allergies!

03:36.883 --> 03:39.719
Sounds inefficient.

03:39.802 --> 03:41.930
[ Gasps ]

03:42.013 --> 03:42.972
Is someone hurt?

03:43.056 --> 03:46.309
[ All shouting "Lava!" ]

03:46.392 --> 03:48.978
To tire them out,
we play Lava Floor.

03:49.062 --> 03:50.980
[ All shouting "Lava!" ]

03:51.064 --> 03:52.649
[ Chuckles ] C'mon, Seth.

03:52.732 --> 03:54.692
You're standing in lava.

03:54.776 --> 03:58.029
[ All shouting "Lava!" ]

03:58.112 --> 03:59.614
The floor is lava!

03:59.697 --> 04:01.991
Oh, no,
don't let it get me!

04:02.075 --> 04:04.369
You know,
if this were real lava,

04:04.452 --> 04:07.205
everything in this room
would be incinerated instantly.

04:07.288 --> 04:09.457
And don't get me
started on magma.

04:09.540 --> 04:12.460
[ Gasps ]
Shamantha is sleeping!

04:12.543 --> 04:14.337
What, who?
The game worked.

04:14.420 --> 04:17.966
After everyone's tired
from playing, we put 'em to bed.

04:18.049 --> 04:19.425
Together: No bed!

04:19.509 --> 04:21.678
Well you see,
at my house --

04:21.761 --> 04:22.679
[ Telephone rings ]

04:22.762 --> 04:25.056
I'll be right back!

04:25.139 --> 04:26.432
Ryan:
<i>Shania, Shania, Shania!</i>

04:26.516 --> 04:27.767
<i>I forgot my fire hose</i>
<i>and accidentally --</i>

04:27.850 --> 04:29.852
Whoa, Ryan, slow down!

04:29.936 --> 04:32.313
There's this fire
and I accidentally brought

04:32.397 --> 04:35.483
my garden hose
instead of my fire hose!

04:35.566 --> 04:38.194
[ Chuckles ]
Classic Ryan!

04:38.277 --> 04:39.904
There's no water pressure.

04:39.988 --> 04:42.156
Shania, just, please,
big, big, big favor --

04:42.240 --> 04:44.951
could you bring my spare
fire hose from home?

04:45.034 --> 04:47.078
Be right there, Ryan.

04:48.997 --> 04:51.332
So uh, chores are done,
huh?

04:51.416 --> 04:54.460
Seth, I need you to watch
my sibs while I'm gone.

04:54.544 --> 04:56.838
And be careful
with little Connor.

04:56.921 --> 04:59.257
He scares easily.

04:59.340 --> 05:02.385
[ Noisemakers blow ]
Ah! [ Screaming ]

05:02.468 --> 05:05.555
Just make sure
they don't hurt themselves.

05:05.638 --> 05:07.473
And don't forget --
Mm-hmm, mm-hmm.

05:07.557 --> 05:10.184
Don't worry
about a thing.

05:10.268 --> 05:12.061
[ Laughter, shouting ]

05:12.145 --> 05:13.438
[ Chuckles ]

05:13.521 --> 05:16.274
Get ready for some
Seth solutions!

05:16.357 --> 05:17.900
<i>Hi-yah!</i>

05:17.984 --> 05:24.073
♪♪

05:24.157 --> 05:25.992
Whew!
Sorry that took so long!

05:26.075 --> 05:27.410
No worries!

05:27.493 --> 05:30.788
I had more than enough time
to solve all of your problems.

05:30.872 --> 05:32.248
What problems?

05:32.331 --> 05:34.959
Welcome to your home,
my friend.

05:36.669 --> 05:38.004
Oh what the --

05:38.087 --> 05:41.215
Sheremy, why is there
a number on your butt?

05:41.299 --> 05:43.718
All those names were
just slowing ya down.

05:43.801 --> 05:45.011
Introducing...

05:45.094 --> 05:46.471
Four, Six, Eight, Nine,

05:46.554 --> 05:49.974
Ten, One, Three, Two, Five,
Seven, and the rest.

05:50.058 --> 05:51.267
What?

05:51.350 --> 05:54.771
Which brings me
to my next Seth solution.

05:54.854 --> 05:57.106
The feeding wheel!

05:57.190 --> 05:59.192
Giving each kid the right amount
of nutrients

05:59.275 --> 06:01.277
and time to chew
and swallow.

06:01.360 --> 06:04.614
This way, the wheel
does the work for you.

06:04.697 --> 06:05.907
Oh, cool!

06:05.990 --> 06:08.326
How'd you account
for their allergies?

06:08.409 --> 06:10.953
Allergies?

06:11.037 --> 06:13.289
Shuri's allergic
to shale.

06:13.372 --> 06:14.957
Huh.
What do ya know?

06:15.041 --> 06:24.509
♪♪

06:24.592 --> 06:28.179
Hmm, no one in my family
has allergies.

06:28.262 --> 06:31.641
Moving right along.

06:31.724 --> 06:33.476
The floor
is no longer lava.

06:33.559 --> 06:35.978
Now we're playing
"Mushrooms of Mavenwood."

06:36.062 --> 06:38.397
It's a two-person
resource-based board game.

06:38.481 --> 06:40.566
Me and my brother play
at my house all the time,

06:40.650 --> 06:41.943
and it's mentally exhausting,

06:42.026 --> 06:43.903
so it's sure to get
these kiddos tired.

06:43.986 --> 06:45.446
Two players?

06:45.530 --> 06:46.989
Where's everyone else?

06:47.073 --> 06:48.324
I'm glad you asked!

06:48.407 --> 06:50.284
They wait their turn
in the holding pen.

06:50.368 --> 06:52.328
[ Siblings babbling ]

06:52.411 --> 06:56.332
But, Seth, if they don't have
an outlet for their energy...

06:56.415 --> 06:57.375
[ Babbling ]

06:57.458 --> 06:58.835
...they're gonna blow!

06:58.918 --> 07:00.711
[ Whimpering ]

07:00.795 --> 07:01.838
[ Explosion ]

07:01.921 --> 07:04.715
[ Screaming ]

07:04.799 --> 07:09.637
♪♪

07:09.720 --> 07:12.348
The floor is lava!

07:12.431 --> 07:15.184
Wheeee!

07:15.268 --> 07:18.563
Aw, they didn't even finish
"Mushrooms of Mavenwood."

07:18.646 --> 07:21.023
It's better when everyone
gets to play.

07:21.107 --> 07:22.859
7, 8, 9...

07:22.942 --> 07:24.235
Where's Connor?

07:24.318 --> 07:27.864
He's drifting off to sleep
with a soothing lullaby.

07:27.947 --> 07:30.199
Seth:<i> Go to sleep. Go to sleep.</i>

07:30.283 --> 07:33.077
<i>Have good dreams.</i>
<i>Have good dreams.</i>

07:33.161 --> 07:35.204
What is that?

07:35.288 --> 07:37.874
Oh, that just keeps Connor
company until he dozes off.

07:37.957 --> 07:40.251
<i>Have good dreams.</i>
<i>Have good dreams.</i>

07:40.334 --> 07:43.754
Oh, yeah.
This baby works like a charm.

07:43.838 --> 07:47.300
[<i> Distorted</i> ]
<i>Go to sleep. Go to sleep.</i>

07:47.383 --> 07:49.719
[ Screaming ]

07:49.802 --> 07:52.221
Seth,
can we talk outside?

07:52.305 --> 07:53.723
I don't know, Seth,

07:53.806 --> 07:56.225
I think you should head
to the premiere by yourself.

07:56.309 --> 07:59.353
But I fixed everything.
We could both go.

07:59.437 --> 08:01.397
There was nothing
to fix.

08:01.480 --> 08:06.027
My family might look messy,
but we get by just fine.

08:06.110 --> 08:07.695
I could have really used
your help,

08:07.778 --> 08:10.239
but you didn't take
any time to listen.

08:10.323 --> 08:12.033
Okay,
but at my house --

08:12.116 --> 08:13.743
This isn't your house!

08:13.826 --> 08:15.953
Your life's different,
and that's okay.

08:16.037 --> 08:19.081
There's no perfect solution
for every problem.

08:19.165 --> 08:22.960
Just...go enjoy
the movie.

08:23.044 --> 08:26.214
Oh, Tiara, I didn't mean
to mess everything up.

08:26.297 --> 08:27.465
What should I do?

08:27.548 --> 08:28.966
<i>I have to stop taking</i>
<i>the lead</i>

08:29.050 --> 08:32.011
<i>so we can truly become</i>
<i>flow compatible!</i>

08:32.094 --> 08:33.221
<i>Ky-yah!</i>

08:33.304 --> 08:35.848
[ Gasps ]
Flow compatibility.

08:35.932 --> 08:39.101
That's it!
[ Screaming ]

08:39.185 --> 08:40.937
Oh, no! Oh, no!
Wait!

08:41.020 --> 08:42.313
[ Screaming ]

08:42.396 --> 08:45.274
Seth, we gotta go get
that wheel!

08:45.358 --> 08:46.275
Of course!

08:46.359 --> 08:48.236
I'll follow your lead,
Shania.

08:48.319 --> 08:57.036
♪♪

08:57.119 --> 08:58.371
Alright, kids.

08:58.454 --> 08:59.914
We've got to get
our siblings back before

08:59.997 --> 09:01.290
Mom and Ryan get home,

09:01.374 --> 09:03.751
or all our butts
are on the burner.

09:03.834 --> 09:06.379
You've gotta be brave
and follow my lead.

09:06.462 --> 09:09.131
Here's what we're making.

09:09.215 --> 09:10.800
[ Siblings "Ooh" ]

09:10.883 --> 09:17.306
♪♪

09:17.390 --> 09:23.729
♪♪

09:23.813 --> 09:25.898
[ Laughs ] Yeah!
Yes!

09:25.982 --> 09:27.567
This is working.

09:27.650 --> 09:29.151
There!

09:29.235 --> 09:35.157
♪♪

09:35.241 --> 09:37.660
[ Screaming ]

09:37.743 --> 09:42.415
♪♪

09:42.498 --> 09:43.708
[ Whistling ]

09:43.791 --> 09:47.169
♪ Friday night, no class
until Monday ♪

09:47.253 --> 09:48.671
Huh? Wha?

09:48.754 --> 09:51.048
[ Screams ]

09:52.800 --> 09:55.594
It's headed straight
for the Fungie Dome!

09:58.389 --> 10:00.099
Ah, we'll never catch
that wheel.

10:00.182 --> 10:01.892
Wait, I've got it.

10:01.976 --> 10:10.818
♪♪

10:10.901 --> 10:11.819
Huh?

10:11.902 --> 10:15.698
Oh, wow!

10:15.781 --> 10:18.492
Seth and Shania:
Flow compatible!

10:22.371 --> 10:24.999
Oh! Oh, thank goodness,
they're safe.

10:27.960 --> 10:30.046
Sorry about
the whole wheel thing.

10:30.129 --> 10:33.507
Hey, see ya at home,
Shania.

10:33.591 --> 10:37.261
Once you listened,
we made a pretty good team.

10:37.345 --> 10:38.220
Yeah.

10:38.304 --> 10:41.640
Too bad
we missed the movie.

10:41.724 --> 10:42.641
[ Both gasp ]

10:42.725 --> 10:45.936
Both: Tiara Thunder!

10:46.020 --> 10:48.731
That's me! You kids want
autographed posters?

10:48.814 --> 10:51.275
I sign all the time.
I love the babies.

10:51.359 --> 10:52.693
Yes, please!

10:52.777 --> 10:55.404
Alright,
who do I make it out to?

10:55.488 --> 10:57.198
Okay, it's to Shubert,
Shelly, Shimmy,

10:57.281 --> 10:59.867
Sean, Shadi,
uh, Shamantha...
Uh-huh, yep. Wow.

10:59.950 --> 11:04.246
Sheremy with two "E's," a "Y,"
a<i> rounded</i> "R."

11:04.330 --> 11:05.706
I need
a bigger picture.

11:05.790 --> 11:11.587
♪♪

11:11.670 --> 11:17.426
♪♪

11:17.510 --> 11:20.096
I love the babies.
